          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Preserving legacy through digitization
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The 1980s and '90s were a whirlwind of growth. Iron Mountain rolled out barcode tracking. <strong>They became the first in the industry to use UPS barcodes for real-time permissions</strong> and expanded into 12 newer US markets. Additionally, they acquired Bell & Howell Records Management in 1988 and went public in 1996. By the end of that decade, they had entered 46 markets and opened their first overseas location with the acquisition of British Data Management Ltd. Their revenue at the time was $423M by 1998.
         </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">By the turn of the new millennium, their <strong>high-profile customers included Bill Gates</strong>, who stored his entire <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-19-04-2025-corbis-photo-archieve?source=website" target="_blank">Corbis photo archive</a>, which included over 11 million iconic images. Music giants like <strong>Sony, Universal, and Warner</strong> keep their master recordings locked away; some even have in-house studios for high-security preservation. The company also safeguards the wills of <strong>Princess Diana, Charles Dickens, and Charles Darwin</strong>.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">While Iron Mountain started underground, it didn’t stay buried in the analog past. As digital transformation gained momentum, the company leaned in. <strong>In 2001, they launched electronic vaulting and digital archives</strong>. By 2013, they had established a dedicated data centers division. Their Iron Cloud platform brought tiered digital storage to enterprise clients, and they even provided secure IT asset disposition services, which helped companies responsibly destroy sensitive materials.</p>
          </mj-text>
          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">The pandemic pivot</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The pandemic was a grim experience for most of the world, but Iron Mountain benefited from it as it forced companies to digitize, organize, and secure data. With millions working from home, companies urgently needed to digitize paper records and shift to cloud-based permission for critical documents. Iron Mountain, already offering scanning, cloud storage, and digital workflow solutions, <strong>became a go-to digital solutions provider during the pandemic</strong>.</p>
          </mj-text>

          <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/pennsylvanias-iron-mountain-mine.png" alt="Pennsylvania’s Iron Mountain mine" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
           <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>Pennsylvania’s Iron Mountain mine. Credits: Getty Images</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>

          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">With employees accessing sensitive information from home, many companies turned to Iron Mountain for secure shredding, remote storage, and compliance assistance. <strong>Their shares saw <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-19-04-2025-significant-growth-in-2020?source=website" target="_blank">significant growth in 2020</a>, rising by over 30%</strong> as businesses rushed to adapt to remote work and digital transformation.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">From fungi to files, vaults to virtual servers, Iron Mountain always kept one foot in the future and built its empire on innovation, foresight, and adaptability.</p>
          </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
